# ~/notes/JAG-LEXICON.org
* -âl
*** Definition
suffix: finite verb marker
*** Related
*** Examples and Usage
- attaches to verbal roots to make finite verbs
  - thiktâlos rorb shevem ::: the sun touches (is shining on, metaphorically) my face
- attaches to adjectives to make a verb meaning "be-adjectival"
  - jûjor shelelâleps ??? Are you okay?
  - shelelâl- be okay
- attaches to numerals
  - totâlosen Mars Wahaz-thor ::: î welk tot
  - one.fin.3pi Mars Wahaz-and ::: there-is planet one
    - totâl- be one
*** Notes

* am
** Definition
particle: appositive particle; namely, even
** Related
- [[î]]
** Examples and Usage
- /târ am balem baleps-thor î bal tot ::/
- lord appos god.1s god.2s-and copula god one
- The Lord Our God and your god are one god. 
- in Jagarôth all words and phrases that are appositive to each other must be separated by *am*. "Our Lord, *even* Jesus Christ" kinda thing.
- another way of saying it: /târ am balem baleps-thor totâlethen/ :::
- totâlethen ::: one.fin.3ps: are one
** Notes
- what about cases like this where there are nested appositives? /The Lord Our God even Jesus Christ./ Like so:
- ((The Lord Our God) even Jesus Christ)
