* jûjor
*** Definition
particle: question marker
*** Related
*** Examples and Usage
- in Jagarôth a question begins with some interrogative word. if question is yes/no (polar), and no interrogative pronoun is available, jûjor begins the clause
- opens questions
- jûj ::: archaic verbal root meaning to speak, to say
- -or ::: interrogative verb ending
- jûjor is basically a transitive verb, imperative mode, where the rest of the clause is the object of the verb root jûj-
- jûjor vê panâleps kenetotem borgîzd mumbik ???
  - question in-past-time see.fin.2s dog.acc.1s city.loc carrion.adj?
  - Did you see my dog in the dead city?
*** Notes

